The paper presents a framework for predicting the presence and properties of edges in graphs based on machine learning and path aggregations. This work is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper applies the framework to the prediction of links and user ratings in social networks, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
